[normal]&#xa0;[bold]John Trevelyan[bold] – Written evidence[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]on the rights of way [bold]provisions[bold] in the Draft Deregulation Bill (Clauses 12 to 18 and Schedule 6)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Amendments to the 'cut-off' provisions
[normal]Clauses
[normal] 12, 13, 14 and Schedule 6 paragraphs 5 and 8 amend the 
[normal]'cut-off' provisions
[normal]. Those provisions are contained in sections 53-56 of the 2000 Act and section 54A of the 1981 Act, but have not yet been commenced.
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Amendments to the public path order application provisions
[normal]Clauses 15 and 17 amend the provisions for applications for public path orders contained in section 118ZA, 118C, 119ZA, 119C and 121A-121E of the Highways Act 1980, none of which have yet been commenced.
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Other proposals
[normal]Other 
[normal]provisions are contained in Clause 16 and Schedule 6 paragraphs 2
[normal],3,4,6,7
[normal] and 9.
