[normal]Definitive map modification
[normal] order
[normal] applications and appeals (Sch
[normal]edule
[normal] 6 para
[normal]graph
[normal]s 4 and 6)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Preliminary assessment of applications
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Examine 
[normal]the 
[normal]application and associated evidence
[normal].
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Research any documentary evidence relied on by the applicant but for which copies have not been supplied under sub-paragraph 1(3).
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Having regard to guidance issued by the Secretary of State, decide whether the application and the evidence show that there is a reasonable basis for the applicant's belief that the map and statement should be modified.
[normal]d)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Notify the applicant of the decision.
[normal]e)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]If the decision is that there is a reasonable basis (
[normal]Defra
[normal] expects 
[normal]this to occur 
[normal]90% of the time), investigate who are the owners and occupiers of all the land to which the application relates, and serve notice on them.
[normal]Dealing with non-determination of an application
